Diffusion effects  Each primary electron is projected to the XY plane and the time line following two gaussian distributions, whose widths are calculated by the distance to the readouts and the gas parameters (drift velocity, longitudinal and transversal diffusion coefficients) generated by Magboltz [73]. The gas parameters are detailed in Table 3.
